You really shouldn't have.

752
00:52:32,600 --> 00:52:37,447
Wow, muck. Oh, you can never have
enough muck, can you, girls?

753
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:39,041
Thanks.

754
00:52:41,280 --> 00:52:43,282
Thank you, thank you, not necessary.

755
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:45,562
Oh, yeah, muck. That's nice too.

756
00:52:47,680 --> 00:52:48,841
Poor Louie.

757
00:52:49,080 --> 00:52:51,970
Oh, I cannot bear to watch this,
my love.

758
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:54,367
I have sacrificed my honour...

759
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:55,806
...for naught.

760
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:08,921
Here we are, Lou. The big show.

761
00:53:09,200 --> 00:53:12,283
I told you I'd take you
right to the top.

762
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:14,323
Whoa. Before you go out there, Lou...

763
00:53:14,560 --> 00:53:17,882
...I have a little contract drawn up
that I need you to sign.

764
00:53:18,080 --> 00:53:20,890
It's no big deal. You're exclusive
to me for a billion years...

765
00:53:21,080 --> 00:53:24,607
...in this or any other galaxy yet to
be discovered, yada-yada-yada.

766
00:53:24,880 --> 00:53:27,167
Just your standard
gentleman's agreement.

767
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:29,562
- Should I'?
- Come on, come on, come on.

768
00:53:29,760 --> 00:53:32,047
With the cash you'll rake in,
you'll have enough...

769
00:53:32,240 --> 00:53:34,686
...to buy a shiny new trumpet
and anything else you want.

770
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:38,680
Enough to repay the music store'?
How can I say no'?

771
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:46,244
Oh. yes!

772
00:53:47,040 --> 00:53:48,644
Ladies and gentlemen...

773
00:53:48,840 --> 00:53:53,767
...put your hands together for
Louie the trumpeter swan.

774
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:10,444
Go, Louie!

775
00:55:00,400 --> 00:55:04,200
Bravo, Lou! They loved you. I got you
booked in the stadium on Saturday...

776
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:06,880
...and I'm very close to
a major network deal.

777
00:55:07,280 --> 00:55:08,645
Here's your salary, kid.

778
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:14,250
Payday!

779
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:21,280
<i>There's a new bird in Boston
and his name is Louie.</i>

780
00:55:21,480 --> 00:55:24,689
<i>He's a trumpeter swan that
really plays the trumpet.</i>

781
00:55:24,880 --> 00:55:25,881
Louie!

782
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:29,050
<i>Tonight, the music of this amazing--</i>

783
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:32,801
You did it, Louie! You did it!
You're famous!

784
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:37,405
You've got a high approval rating,
my friend.

785
00:55:37,760 --> 00:55:38,568
Well done.

786
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:41,644
Message from the Internut.

787
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:47,365
- This is terrible news!
- What could it be'?

788
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:48,800
The message is this:

789
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:52,402
Your girlfriend is gonna marry
the crooner...

790
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:56,491
...with the greasy feathers. Right,
tomorrow. I got it! I did it!

791
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:58,201
Serena and Boyd'?

792
00:55:58,400 --> 00:55:59,640
Why didn't you come sooner?

793
00:55:59,880 --> 00:56:02,406
So blame me. I made
a few nut stops, okay?

794
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:04,769
Go to her, youngster.

795
00:56:04,960 --> 00:56:07,645
You might be behind in the polls...

796
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:11,890
...but remember, it's not over until
election day!

797
00:56:12,080 --> 00:56:13,081
Good luck, Louie.

798
00:56:13,440 --> 00:56:14,521
Lou, did you see the--'?

799
00:56:15,840 --> 00:56:18,525
Not so fast, you fern-eating ingrate!

800
00:56:18,720 --> 00:56:23,009
You, Lou, are my property!
You're not going nowhere.

801
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:25,726
I'll clip those wings
so you'll never fly again!

802
00:56:25,960 --> 00:56:28,122
- He's got scissors!
- I hate scissors!

803
00:56:28,320 --> 00:56:31,324
Hate to do it to you, Louie,
but money is money!

804
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:32,761
Stop, you!

805
00:56:36,640 --> 00:56:38,404
Hey, you, over here! Hey, me!

806
00:56:40,600 --> 00:56:44,002
Call my aides, I'm going in!

807
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:47,843
That's all right. I'm unharmed.

808
00:56:48,040 --> 00:56:49,246
Take this!

809
00:56:49,680 --> 00:56:50,727
Get away from me!

810
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:52,490
Free that swan!

811
00:56:54,080 --> 00:56:58,051
Go, Louie! Fly like the wind!

812
00:56:58,440 --> 00:57:02,047
- Are we nice and comfy there?
- Come on!

813
00:57:04,080 --> 00:57:07,801
Quiet, it's about to start.
Serena, here she comes.

814
00:57:13,440 --> 00:57:14,441
Oh, no!

815
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:15,841
Traffic!

816
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:26,043
Whoa! Sorry Mr. Presidents.
I've got to hurry.

817
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:28,683
Oh, heaven knows...

818
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:31,531
...I have known sadness
in my lifetime.

819
00:57:31,800 --> 00:57:34,849
But never a sorrow such as this.

820
00:57:35,040 --> 00:57:37,042
Louie will be so...

821
00:57:37,240 --> 00:57:38,651
...heartbroken.

822
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:46,045
Oh, no, not now.

823
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:49,490
Do you, Boyd...

824
00:57:49,680 --> 00:57:51,205
...take Serena...

825
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:54,165
...to be your lifelong mate'?

826
00:57:54,680 --> 00:57:58,241
I do-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh!

827
00:57:59,080 --> 00:58:02,368
And do you, Serena...

828
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:03,766
...take Boyd...

829
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:07,203
...to be your lifelong mate'?

830
00:58:13,240 --> 00:58:15,607
Whoever you are, wait your turn.

831
00:58:15,960 --> 00:58:18,645
I haven't gotten to the part
about objections.

832
00:58:21,440 --> 00:58:23,283
- Louie!
- Louie!

833
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,050
Oh. yeah!

834
00:58:31,480 --> 00:58:32,891
That's beautiful.

835
00:58:33,080 --> 00:58:36,721
- Okay, okay, what does it say'?
- It says that...

836
00:58:36,920 --> 00:58:38,843
...Louie is mine...

837
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:43,244
...and I am his...

838
00:58:43,560 --> 00:58:44,561
...forever.

839
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,089
So you can talk now, huh'?

840
00:58:48,280 --> 00:58:51,090
Let's see what you have to say
without your stupid horn!

841
00:58:51,280 --> 00:58:52,406
Oh, no, my voice!

842
00:58:55,880 --> 00:58:59,362
There goes your love call, songbird.

843
00:58:59,560 --> 00:59:02,848
Now get off my lake!
And don't come back!

844
00:59:14,280 --> 00:59:15,964
Dangerous curves ahead.

845
00:59:16,160 --> 00:59:18,731
Too bad old Boyd
never learned to read.

846
00:59:25,240 --> 00:59:26,082
Help!

847
00:59:26,280 --> 00:59:27,850
Somebody, help!

848
00:59:32,240 --> 00:59:34,242
Daddy, I love Louie.

849
00:59:34,440 --> 00:59:35,646
And he loves me.

850
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:41,086
I know, Serena.
I heard him loud and clear.

851
00:59:49,360 --> 00:59:53,410
<i>When the moon would rise
I'd close my eyes</i>

852
00:59:53,600 --> 00:59:57,082
<i>And dream of you and me</i>

853
00:59:57,280 --> 01:00:01,365
<i>And tomorrow's when
I'd dream again</i>

854
01:00:01,560 --> 01:00:04,404
<i>And in my dreams I'd see</i>

855
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:08,682
<i>We'd fly</i> away

856
01:00:09,160 --> 01:00:12,721
<i>To a wondrous brand-new day</i>

857
01:00:13,280 --> 01:00:16,841
<i>And we'd sail up there so high</i>

858
01:00:17,640 --> 01:00:20,564
<i>We could touch the sky</i>

859
01:00:21,640 --> 01:00:24,883
<i>We'd fly, we'd soar</i>

860
01:00:25,360 --> 01:00:28,807
<i>Just you forevermore</i>

861
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:33,483
<i>And the stars shine in your eyes</i>

862
01:00:33,680 --> 01:00:35,921
<i>We can touch the sky</i>

863
01:00:36,680 --> 01:00:38,170
<i>You and me</i>

864
01:00:39,880 --> 01:00:44,249
<i>Yeah, yeah</i>

865
01:00:46,400 --> 01:00:51,281
<i>And we'll dance upon the clouds</i>

866
01:00:54,840 --> 01:00:58,890
<i>And I'll love you till I die</i>

867
01:00:59,400 --> 01:01:03,041
<i>We could touch the sky</i>

868
01:01:03,480 --> 01:01:07,121
<i>You and me</i>

869
01:01:16,880 --> 01:01:19,884
I never heard your music
until today, son.

870
01:01:20,080 --> 01:01:23,209
Now I feel your voice in my heart.

871
01:01:23,840 --> 01:01:26,241
To think I once thought you were...

872
01:01:26,440 --> 01:01:27,362
...defective.

873
01:01:27,880 --> 01:01:30,406
Forgive me, Louie.
How little I knew.

874
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:34,570
It seems so long ago, that day
in the music store...

875
01:01:34,760 --> 01:01:38,242
...when I took... When I--

876
01:01:41,880 --> 01:01:43,041
Money?

877
01:01:43,760 --> 01:01:46,445
Why are you giving me money'?

878
01:01:47,760 --> 01:01:48,966
To pay for the trumpet.

879
01:01:49,280 --> 01:01:52,170
Oh, Louie, this is the gift
of a lifetime!

880
01:01:52,960 --> 01:01:55,008
Onward, my son...

881
01:01:55,200 --> 01:01:57,123
...to Billings!

882
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,723
Ah, here is Billings.

883
01:02:02,920 --> 01:02:04,649
The scene of my crime.

884
01:02:07,280 --> 01:02:11,365
Thank you, Louie, for giving me
the chance to redeem my honour.

885
01:02:17,280 --> 01:02:20,329
It's that swan thief!

886
01:02:22,680 --> 01:02:23,522
No!

887
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:27,001
- He's got a gun!
- No! Don't shoot!

888
01:02:27,480 --> 01:02:28,288
Father!

889
01:02:32,560 --> 01:02:34,369
The end is near.

890
01:02:34,560 --> 01:02:39,168
Man, in his folly,
has given me a mortal wound.

891
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:44,731
Oh, goodbye, beautiful world.

892
01:02:44,920 --> 01:02:48,447
Farewell, sweet springtimes
I have known.

893
01:02:48,840 --> 01:02:53,243
Adieu, loyal wife and loving children.

894
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:58,049
Now I die.

895
01:02:58,240 --> 01:02:59,480
Gracefully...

896
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:01,045
...as really...

897
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:03,242
only a swan...

898
01:03:03,840 --> 01:03:04,762
...can.

899
01:03:09,840 --> 01:03:12,605
He's dead. The bird is dead.

900
01:03:13,200 --> 01:03:14,486
Father.

901
01:03:15,080 --> 01:03:16,650
Oh, Father.

902
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:19,047
I'm so sorry, Louie.

903
01:03:19,800 --> 01:03:23,486
Look what you've done.
You killed a trumpeter swan.

904
01:03:24,080 --> 01:03:26,208
These birds are endangered!

905
01:03:27,240 --> 01:03:29,641
This endangered bird...

906
01:03:29,840 --> 01:03:32,127
...swiped a trumpet from my store.

907
01:03:33,280 --> 01:03:35,248
"To the storekeeper of Billings...

908
01:03:35,440 --> 01:03:39,490
...enclosed please find
a whole lot of money.

909
01:03:39,680 --> 01:03:42,684
This will be more than enough
to pay for the trumpet...

910
01:03:42,880 --> 01:03:45,360
...and the damage to the store.

911
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:48,450
I am an honourable swan."

912
01:03:49,200 --> 01:03:51,487
Looks like you made
a big mistake, buddy.

913
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:55,684
All right, people, stand back.

914
01:03:55,880 --> 01:03:58,690
Could you let us through here,
please? We have an emergency.

915
01:04:01,880 --> 01:04:03,484
It's just a superficial wound.

916
01:04:05,200 --> 01:04:07,806
It is'? What's that? Say what?

917
01:04:08,040 --> 01:04:09,405
He must've just fainted.

918
01:04:10,760 --> 01:04:12,842
I have been at death's door...

919
01:04:13,040 --> 01:04:14,166
...and now...

920
01:04:14,360 --> 01:04:16,169
...I am reviving.

921
01:04:16,360 --> 01:04:19,284
I shall once again glide gracefully...

922
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:21,562
...on the ponds of the world.

923
01:04:22,480 --> 01:04:25,165
I want this money used to help save...

924
01:04:25,680 --> 01:04:27,967
...the trumpeters.

925
01:04:28,280 --> 01:04:30,362
That's what I'm gonna do
when I grow up.

926
01:04:30,880 --> 01:04:31,961
I promise you, Louie.

927
01:04:32,480 --> 01:04:33,891
I'll protect you.

928
01:04:34,440 --> 01:04:36,442
You're a friend forever.

929
01:04:41,840 --> 01:04:45,606
Darling, you're back.
You're back! How did it go'?

930
01:04:46,040 --> 01:04:47,644
How did it go'?

931
01:04:48,640 --> 01:04:50,768
"How did it go?" you ask.

932
01:04:50,960 --> 01:04:53,930
There was gunfire! There was blood!

933
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:56,481
No, no, not Louie!

934
01:04:56,680 --> 01:04:59,047
Not to worry, Serena.
It was I who died.

935
01:05:00,240 --> 01:05:01,446
- Serena.
- Louie!

936
01:05:03,760 --> 01:05:07,287
At first, I felt an agonizing pain
in my left shoulder...

937
01:05:07,480 --> 01:05:11,485
...which I've always considered the
more beautiful of my two shoulders.

938
01:05:11,680 --> 01:05:15,048
Blood gushed from my wound
in torrents...

939
01:05:15,240 --> 01:05:18,403
...and I sank gracefully
to the sidewalk.

940
01:05:18,600 --> 01:05:21,171
The police arrived. Dozens of them.

941
01:05:21,360 --> 01:05:24,170
How did you know all this
if you were unconscious?

942
01:05:24,880 --> 01:05:28,009
I wish you wouldn't interrupt when
I'm telling the story of my death.

943
01:05:28,280 --> 01:05:32,330
Oh, of course. But I'm glad to
see you home safe.

944
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:35,251
I always miss you when you're gone.

945
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:40,481
Although I was faint,
I passed out with dignity.

946
01:05:40,680 --> 01:05:42,284
My life flashed before me:

947
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:45,290
The ponds I have known, the winters
I have weathered...

948
01:05:45,480 --> 01:05:48,211
...the summers of my wanton youth.

949
01:05:48,400 --> 01:05:50,562
I was certain my time had come...

950
01:05:50,880 --> 01:05:53,042
...when, suddenly...

951
01:05:53,760 --> 01:05:55,250
...eggs!

952
01:05:59,040 --> 01:06:00,690
My goodness.

953
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:02,564
Eggs!

954
01:06:02,760 --> 01:06:04,285
That's right, my love.

955
01:06:04,480 --> 01:06:05,891
Louie and Serena...

956
01:06:06,080 --> 01:06:08,560
...are going to have a family.

957
01:06:08,720 --> 01:06:09,721
Octuplets.

958
01:06:12,800 --> 01:06:15,167
- I'm speechless!
- It's about time.

959
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:31,360
There's nothing in this world
I like more...

960
01:06:31,560 --> 01:06:34,689
...than the sound of the trumpet
of the swan.

961
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:39,081
How lucky we are to inhabit
this beautiful earth.

962
01:06:39,280 --> 01:06:43,285
How incredible it is to look forward
to another night of sleep...

963
01:06:43,480 --> 01:06:46,211
...and the light that
returns with the day.

964
01:06:47,560 --> 01:06:52,487
I wonder why the sun comes up
every morning after the darkness.

965
01:07:10,440 --> 01:07:12,647
Welcome, my children.

966
01:11:34,240 --> 01:11:35,241
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group